2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses tools from stochastic geometry to analyze and optimize the successful transmission probability, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers optimization problems to maximize the successful transmission probability, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with caching and transmission of files, which can be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper considers optimization problems, which can be related to game theory.
